That PR does a massive renaming for `Statement`'s fields according to our code convention and updates the docs/comments to reflect that statements are not `GenTree` nodes anymore.

Semantic changes exist only in https://github.com/dotnet/coreclr/pull/26876/commits/4c7712fca7d40983e9afeb302909328c8e8f2567 morph.cpp:
`stmt->gtStmtExpr = tree = morph;` -> `stmt->SetRootTree(morphedTree);` because that was the last use of `tree`.


Closes #25899 .

`m_compilerAdded` deletion would be in another PR later.

No Pin/asm diffs (x64/x86 Windows).

Changes:
[Delete a leftover for STMT and update dump examples.](https://github.com/dotnet/coreclr/pull/26876/commits/c8ea338ca28e7f9406f6f19e4cafcbf822838b9a);

[Prepare `GetNextStmt` and `GetPrevStmt` to be used as main read accessors.](https://github.com/dotnet/coreclr/pull/26876/commits/a868e5a073f6fe6144395fc407047ec685a0f2ab);

[Rename `Statement->gtNext` to `m_nextStmt` and make it private.](https://github.com/dotnet/coreclr/pull/26876/commits/7e96ca650f90dbf5ffbcd63b41249dc3f5c0f307);

[Rename `Statement->gtPrev` to `m_prev` and make it private.](https://github.com/dotnet/coreclr/pull/26876/commits/9ac81c6f515b1883d5baea913e7c6ba7f290bd10);

[Rename `gtStmtLastILoffs` to `m_lastILOffset` and make it private.](https://github.com/dotnet/coreclr/pull/26876/commits/e10487d26d6b51c2c22fb91f708efd3d323c9eee); 

[Rename `gtStmtILoffsx` to `m_ILOffsetX` and make it private.](https://github.com/dotnet/coreclr/pull/26876/commits/4966759af565a84c94468b985a97f2fff2322c78); 

[Rename `compilerAdded` to `m_compilerAdded` and make it private.](https://github.com/dotnet/coreclr/pull/26876/commits/a1adba2f01de78409cf8c9ae817f3ec9ad8b99cf);

[Rename `gtInlineContext` to `m_inlineContext` and make it private.](https://github.com/dotnet/coreclr/pull/26876/commits/d6e9226f4ec2c32a2b45707d06004d31275e6129:);

[Rename `gtStmtList` to `m_treeList` and make it private.](https://github.com/dotnet/coreclr/pull/26876/commits/d6e9226f4ec2c32a2b45707d06004d31275e6129);

[Rename `gtStmtExpr` to `m_rootTree` and make it private.](https://github.com/dotnet/coreclr/pull/26876/commits/4c7712fca7d40983e9afeb302909328c8e8f2567:);

[Update the class layout according to our spec.](https://github.com/dotnet/coreclr/pull/26876/commits/9df86d1751646919b90daccc2f285a9fa9529a67);

[Update the docs.](https://github.com/dotnet/coreclr/pull/26876/commits/d00d2510680a9bdcfd7ef397349c573ac993a099).

This will allow us to save ~1% of Jit memory usage (according to my raw prototype), clean many noway_asserts, switches, and checks;
It will make code more readable and make statements more flexible. 

See discussion in https://github.com/dotnet/coreclr/pull/22963 (https://github.com/dotnet/coreclr/pull/22963#issuecomment-478165359).

The steps are:

- [x] Delete unused function and flags (addressed by https://github.com/dotnet/coreclr/pull/25886);
- [x] Separate ILGenOffset from Statements (#25898);
- [x] Do now reference GenTreeStmt as GenTree (#25898);
- [x] Separate bbTreeList and bbStmtList (#26092);
- [x] Do not inherit GenTreeStmt from GenTree (#26092);
- [ ] Massive renaming for the new Statement class and its fields;

Additional steps:

- [ ] Delete extra fields in stmt (like `getPrevStmt`, `IsPhiDefnStmt`);
- [x] Return void from `GenTreeStmt* fgInsertStmtSomewhere`;
- [x] Return debug number for statements; 
- [x] Retun a print function for statements;
- [ ] Think how to get rid of `bool compilerAdded`;
- [x] Add iterators.

